The paper deals with multiagent systems and their collective behavior, which falls under the category of Multiagent Systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the optimization of tracking performance, which is related to control systems (cs.SY). The use of communication-graph topology and distributed estimation techniques suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of spectral properties of a directed graph suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
